cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper investigates the performance of epidemic routing in mobile social networks. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper focuses on mobile social networks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a Stochastic Reward Net (SRN) model to evaluate the performance of epidemic routing. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is relevant as the paper analyzes the behavior of multiple nodes in a network. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is relevant as the paper is concerned with evaluating the performance of epidemic routing.
